Responsibilities : 
Work with product owner and team to maintain and prioritize backlog 
Schedule and conduct Scrum events 
Coordinate with development team to remove impediments and track delivery 
Faciliate meetings/discussions with multiple integration teams 
Working knowledge of Azure DevOps or similar tools to implement and track Agile delivery 
Provide training to the Business product owners and/or technical teams in Agile Scrum and tools when needed 
Should be able to work parallely on multiple project teams acting as a Scrum Master, providing business analysis and consultation as needed to meet Client objectives. 
Business analysis and requirement elicitation skills 
Test planning and coordination working with the business and technical teams 
Strong communication, interpersonal and problem solving skills 
Knowledge in CPRD domain is a plus 
2 years in Scrum Master and Business Analysis experience 
Over all industry experience of 4 years. 
